cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the optimization of content delivery time by leveraging cooperative transmission and multicasting opportunities, which are key concepts in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a cloud-RAN architecture with cache-enabled ENs and end-users, which involves networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers a system with multiple components (ENs, end-users, central server) and proposes a scheme to optimize its performance, which falls under the purview of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with content delivery, which is a key aspect of multimedia systems. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed caching and delivery scheme involving multiple ENs and end-users, which falls under the purview of distributed computing.
